unicode.value: In this lesson, you will learn topic-specific vocabulary on the subject of food (meat, fish, vegetables and fruit) and ways of cooking. You will revise the pronunciation of adjectives ending in -ed and finally you will have to read a text on some restaurant reviews in addition to some speaking practice about food.

In this lesson, you will: 

  • learn topic-specific vocabulary on the subject of food and ways of cooking
  • practise pronunciation of adjectives ending in -ed
  • read a text on some restaurant reviews
  • have some speaking practice about food
In the following sections, you will learn vocabulary related to food.

Listen and repeat

Pork

          

Chicken


Lamb

Salmon


Tuna

Listen and repeat

Aubergine


Green beans


Courgette


Red pepper


Carrots

Listen and repeat

Watermelon 


Apple




Avocado




Strawberries




Raspberries



Peach
Read the definitions of these words

boiled

cooked in water that is extremely hot

fried

cooked in hot oil or fat

roasted

cooked in an oven or over a fire

grilled

cooked over fire or hot coals, usually on a metal frame

baked

 cooked  in an oven without extra fat or liquid

Listen to the pronunciation of the -ed ending in the following words and repeat.

boiled

roasted

grilled

fried

baked

Remember:

The final -ed is pronounced /d/ after voiced consonants and vowels, /t/ after voiceless consonants and /id/ after the sounds /t/ or /d/.
Read the following texts and answer the questions.

Duración:
25 minutos
